These results were achieved consistently on Linux Mint 17.3 (Cinnamon 64-bit), built with gcc version 4.8.4 (Ubuntu 4.8.4-2ubuntu 1~14.04.3). On Arch Linux (updated 2017-03-13), the PoC code did not crash on every run. In both cases, the following were built:

mruby SHA: 191ee2596cc7b22e3213d82bab1a48ae6152b475
mruby-engine SHA: 09be20e67888b20bebf9b0588bc3cbec7f55325f

The gdb output shown for mruby-engine uses a mruby submodule commit (4ab70294ea01cbaf6bdbfbea5bbd854f6661cfd8) several commits behind the one we used to test mruby on its own. The crash is present in 191ee2596cc7b22e3213d82bab1a48ae6152b475 as well, though this time in vm.c:1806 (mrb_vm_exec):

    1804│         regs[acc] = v;
    1805│       }
    1806├>      JUMP;
    1807│     }

(gdb) print *pc
Cannot access memory at address 0x0
